Manchester City must make changes in all areas of the pitch in order to sustain a challenge at home and in Europe next season, according to Rodney Marsh.

The club legend branded the signing of defender Eliaquim Mangala as 'terrible' and said star striker Sergio Aguero is 'having a very ordinary time' despite scoring 23 goals this season.

Former England striker Marsh, who played for City between 1972 and 1976, also predicted manager Manuel Pellegrini will be sacked in the summer unless they retain the Premier League.

